1
00:00:05,320 --> 00:00:07,640
Welcome to Balance Island.

2
00:00:08,000 --> 00:00:08,960
I am the Island.

3
00:00:08,960 --> 00:00:10,400
(Island)
Neither an islander,

4
00:00:10,640 --> 00:00:12,240
nor the playful kind of isle.

5
00:00:12,320 --> 00:00:14,040
I am the Balance Island.

6
00:00:14,600 --> 00:00:17,400
(Balance Island)
People always call me a paradise for romance.

7
00:00:17,400 --> 00:00:19,280
♪Love me or him♪

8
00:00:19,280 --> 00:00:21,920
And I keep witnessing their love stories.

9
00:00:22,720 --> 00:00:23,750
When they first meet.

10
00:00:25,520 --> 00:00:27,640
The first girl I felt something for was you.

11
00:00:27,640 --> 00:00:29,400
You'd totally be my type.

12
00:00:29,400 --> 00:00:30,540
Get to know each other.

13
00:00:30,640 --> 00:00:31,680
So when are you going

14
00:00:31,680 --> 00:00:32,360
to Hawaii?

15
00:00:32,400 --> 00:00:33,400
When we both can go.

16
00:00:33,400 --> 00:00:33,920
Sounds good.

17
00:00:33,920 --> 00:00:35,120
The day they fall in love.

18
00:00:35,120 --> 00:00:35,800
And you say...

19
00:00:35,800 --> 00:00:36,360
Honey.

20
00:00:36,360 --> 00:00:37,440
I like you.

21
00:00:37,440 --> 00:00:38,440
Let's be together.

22
00:00:38,440 --> 00:00:39,400
When she comes over,

23
00:00:39,400 --> 00:00:40,680
I'm going to make things clear.

24
00:00:40,680 --> 00:00:42,680
I'll give her all of me.

25
00:00:43,390 --> 00:00:44,180
Love

26
00:00:44,430 --> 00:00:46,180
is so tricky.

27
00:00:46,760 --> 00:00:48,800
Have you felt a spark for me?

28
00:00:49,440 --> 00:00:51,920
(Love, rose, thorns)
Is it a rose or is it thorns?

29
00:00:52,360 --> 00:00:53,360
I'm crazy about you.

30
00:00:53,430 --> 00:00:54,240
What's with tomorrow?

31
00:00:54,240 --> 00:00:55,920
Probably a mix of complicated feelings.

32
00:00:55,920 --> 00:00:56,680
I think.

33
00:00:56,680 --> 00:00:58,840
I could give up my life now for you.

34
00:00:58,840 --> 00:01:00,000
I don't want to.

35
00:01:00,000 --> 00:01:00,440
Yang.

36
00:01:00,470 --> 00:01:01,080
Let's break up.

37
00:01:01,400 --> 00:01:02,800
Saying this now feels...

38
00:01:02,800 --> 00:01:03,680
Too much?

39
00:01:03,680 --> 00:01:04,480
Yeah, way too much.

40
00:01:04,480 --> 00:01:06,000
Wanting to confess is a good thing.

41
00:01:06,000 --> 00:01:07,240
You really think so?

42
00:01:07,240 --> 00:01:09,840
Today's their last day here with me.

43
00:01:09,840 --> 00:01:13,000
I'll be witnessing their final decision.

44
00:01:14,120 --> 00:01:15,440
Wanna join me?

45
00:01:15,460 --> 00:01:19,100
=Episode 10 (Part 1)=
=She's Unique=

46
00:01:19,340 --> 00:01:26,780
(Countdown to the Final Confession)

47
00:01:27,640 --> 00:01:29,320
What you said to me yesterday,

48
00:01:29,320 --> 00:01:31,560
honestly, it hurt.

49
00:01:31,560 --> 00:01:32,440
No.

50
00:01:32,440 --> 00:01:34,320
I thought that's what you meant.

51
00:01:34,320 --> 00:01:35,440
When did I ever say

52
00:01:35,440 --> 00:01:36,520
that kind of thing?

53
00:01:36,840 --> 00:01:37,760
I said a few things,

54
00:01:37,760 --> 00:01:39,720
and you said, 'Yang, that's too much.'

55
00:01:39,880 --> 00:01:40,800
Like, way too much.

56
00:01:41,240 --> 00:01:42,200
Yang.

57
00:01:42,200 --> 00:01:43,440
(After the date last night)

58
00:01:43,440 --> 00:01:44,320
What you're saying,

59
00:01:44,320 --> 00:01:45,960
even though it's very...

60
00:01:45,960 --> 00:01:47,000
beautiful...

61
00:01:48,400 --> 00:01:49,640
So if it's off the show,

62
00:01:49,640 --> 00:01:50,560
it feels like

63
00:01:50,560 --> 00:01:52,240
I lose that spark.

64
00:01:52,240 --> 00:01:53,680
Zhao Enda might just be the same.

65
00:01:53,680 --> 00:01:54,600
Maybe it's not exactly

66
00:01:54,600 --> 00:01:56,680
the ideal goal I imagined.

67
00:01:56,680 --> 00:01:58,800
I'm actually fine with that.

68
00:02:00,040 --> 00:02:01,200
Hearing you think that way,

69
00:02:01,200 --> 00:02:03,120
kinda freaks me out.

70
00:02:03,360 --> 00:02:04,960
I thought you felt that way.

71
00:02:04,960 --> 00:02:06,360
Yeah, the fact that you thought

72
00:02:06,360 --> 00:02:07,520
that's what I meant

73
00:02:07,520 --> 00:02:08,480
scares me.

74
00:02:08,480 --> 00:02:09,440
Because I never even

75
00:02:09,440 --> 00:02:10,880
went that far in my thoughts.

76
00:02:13,640 --> 00:02:15,200
That's why I said you're a rational man,

77
00:02:15,200 --> 00:02:16,240
but honestly, I'm not.

78
00:02:17,760 --> 00:02:19,000
I thought you were rational too.

79
00:02:20,320 --> 00:02:22,040
It means you don't really know me yet.

80
00:02:23,480 --> 00:02:24,600
Right?

81
00:02:27,040 --> 00:02:28,280
What Enda said last night

82
00:02:28,280 --> 00:02:30,040
caught me off guard.

83
00:02:30,040 --> 00:02:32,080
I wanted to talk to him about what I think.

84
00:02:32,400 --> 00:02:34,400
Just to make sure.

85
00:02:38,160 --> 00:02:39,320
So, how much do you like me,

86
00:02:39,320 --> 00:02:40,400
on a scale from one to ten?

87
00:02:40,520 --> 00:02:42,520
At the moment?

88
00:02:44,280 --> 00:02:45,440
I'd say around eight or nine.

89
00:02:48,840 --> 00:02:51,160
And the missing one or two points...

90
00:02:53,600 --> 00:02:56,240
Because of the long-distance thing?

91
00:02:58,840 --> 00:03:00,320
Maybe that was before yesterday.

92
00:03:00,520 --> 00:03:02,480
I think, for me,

93
00:03:02,480 --> 00:03:03,440
you...

94
00:03:04,040 --> 00:03:04,960
Your feelings for me

95
00:03:04,960 --> 00:03:07,000
might be half emotional and half rational.

96
00:03:07,000 --> 00:03:08,120
About fifty-fifty, maybe.

97
00:03:08,200 --> 00:03:09,420
Neither the emotional side

98
00:03:09,440 --> 00:03:10,940
nor the rational side stands out more.

99
00:03:11,160 --> 00:03:12,040
As for how I feel,

100
00:03:12,040 --> 00:03:14,120
it's probably also half reason, half emotion.

101
00:03:14,840 --> 00:03:16,280
Maybe when we meet and hang out,

102
00:03:16,280 --> 00:03:17,480
I get more emotional.

103
00:03:17,880 --> 00:03:19,440
But when I'm alone,

104
00:03:19,440 --> 00:03:20,400
I still think about you.

105
00:03:20,400 --> 00:03:22,240
It's more rationally.

106
00:03:22,320 --> 00:03:23,520
And those rational thoughts

107
00:03:23,600 --> 00:03:26,280
aren't meant to kill my feelings for you,

108
00:03:26,750 --> 00:03:27,520
but make me wonder,

109
00:03:27,520 --> 00:03:30,120
how to keep this relationship strong.

110
00:03:34,080 --> 00:03:34,480
Why

111
00:03:34,480 --> 00:03:35,840
did I suddenly

112
00:03:35,840 --> 00:03:37,400
say those things last night?

113
00:03:37,400 --> 00:03:38,360
Well...

114
00:03:38,360 --> 00:03:39,400
Which things? What exactly?

115
00:03:39,400 --> 00:03:40,680
You said quite a lot.

116
00:03:40,680 --> 00:03:41,320
I did.

117
00:03:41,320 --> 00:03:44,440
Everything I said last night

118
00:03:44,440 --> 00:03:46,520
was like

119
00:03:46,520 --> 00:03:48,040
ninety percent rational.

120
00:03:48,280 --> 00:03:48,680
Yeah.

121
00:03:48,680 --> 00:03:49,200
Basically.

122
00:03:49,200 --> 00:03:50,240
I was really shocked.

123
00:03:53,370 --> 00:03:54,200
Because in real life,

124
00:03:54,200 --> 00:03:55,680
we still have to get back

125
00:03:56,020 --> 00:03:57,400
- to that kind of state.
- Yeah.

126
00:03:57,400 --> 00:03:58,090
- So...
- Yes.

127
00:03:59,960 --> 00:04:01,240
I was afraid you might really

128
00:04:01,240 --> 00:04:03,040
be too emotional on the island.

129
00:04:03,040 --> 00:04:03,960
When we returned,

130
00:04:03,960 --> 00:04:04,380
it's like...

131
00:04:04,410 --> 00:04:05,440
I already told you,

132
00:04:05,440 --> 00:04:06,720
I'm an emotional person.

133
00:04:06,720 --> 00:04:09,400
At least I'm aware of that.

134
00:04:09,600 --> 00:04:10,760
At the time, I thought

135
00:04:11,400 --> 00:04:12,760
your emotions

136
00:04:12,760 --> 00:04:14,360
completely took over your mind.

137
00:04:14,360 --> 00:04:15,600
And it's like,

138
00:04:15,600 --> 00:04:16,000
okay,

139
00:04:16,000 --> 00:04:18,000
I don't care about any real problems,

140
00:04:18,000 --> 00:04:19,960
but you always end up caring.

141
00:04:19,960 --> 00:04:21,520
But when you start to truly care,

142
00:04:21,520 --> 00:04:22,680
will you actually like me?

143
00:04:22,680 --> 00:04:25,280
I just want you to think about that.

144
00:04:26,840 --> 00:04:28,840
But you have emotional side too.

145
00:04:28,840 --> 00:04:30,760
It's not all just rational.

146
00:04:34,240 --> 00:04:34,960
Right?

147
00:04:34,960 --> 00:04:36,400
Do you even have a sensitive side?

148
00:04:36,400 --> 00:04:37,120
Yeah, I do.

149
00:04:37,120 --> 00:04:38,880
You're more emotional in real life, right?

150
00:04:38,960 --> 00:04:41,400
On the island, you have
to think rationally about survival.

151
00:04:41,680 --> 00:04:43,520
In regular life, survival isn't the question.

152
00:04:43,520 --> 00:04:44,190
If love's gone,

153
00:04:44,200 --> 00:04:45,120
just walk away.

154
00:04:45,320 --> 00:04:45,840
No big deal.

155
00:04:45,840 --> 00:04:46,210
Not that.

156
00:04:46,220 --> 00:04:48,520
I feel emotions run higher on the island.

157
00:04:48,840 --> 00:04:49,920
Emotions run heavier there.

158
00:04:49,920 --> 00:04:51,680
Because the environment sparks them.

159
00:04:52,080 --> 00:04:52,480
Yeah.

160
00:04:52,480 --> 00:04:53,560
It pushes you toward it.

161
00:04:53,560 --> 00:04:54,480
Stay or leave.

162
00:04:54,480 --> 00:04:56,320
Honestly, I never really cared about it.

163
00:04:56,320 --> 00:04:58,000
I feel like rationality on the island

164
00:04:58,520 --> 00:04:59,360
weighs less.

165
00:05:05,960 --> 00:05:07,080
When two people get together,

166
00:05:07,080 --> 00:05:08,100
there are always problems.

167
00:05:08,120 --> 00:05:09,360
Even without distance.

168
00:05:09,800 --> 00:05:11,120
Real life gets in the way.

169
00:05:11,120 --> 00:05:12,560
Unless you're a perfect match,

170
00:05:12,560 --> 00:05:14,200
but that doesn't happen for most people,

171
00:05:14,600 --> 00:05:15,240
actually.

172
00:05:15,360 --> 00:05:16,720
Besides, why call it love?

173
00:05:16,720 --> 00:05:19,160
It has to be driven by emotions.

174
00:05:19,160 --> 00:05:20,240
If it's purely rational,

175
00:05:20,240 --> 00:05:21,360
that's not dating.

176
00:05:21,580 --> 00:05:22,600
That's financial planning.

177
00:05:24,360 --> 00:05:25,720
That's risk management.

178
00:05:25,920 --> 00:05:26,880
Right?

179
00:05:27,760 --> 00:05:28,640
Right.

180
00:05:30,280 --> 00:05:31,760
I don't want that.

181
00:05:41,040 --> 00:05:41,840
Of course.

182
00:05:42,680 --> 00:05:44,440
I didn't come here to play it safe.

183
00:05:44,440 --> 00:05:44,800
No need.

184
00:05:44,800 --> 00:05:46,240
I said that yesterday.

185
00:05:46,240 --> 00:05:48,520
It's kind of like going on a blind date,

186
00:05:48,520 --> 00:05:50,520
and meeting someone
who seems totally suitable,

187
00:05:50,520 --> 00:05:51,840
but I don't feel anything for him.

188
00:05:51,920 --> 00:05:53,720
He checks every box, every condition fits,

189
00:05:53,720 --> 00:05:55,760
yet I can't find one reason to say no,

190
00:05:55,760 --> 00:05:56,920
except that I don't like him.

191
00:06:00,160 --> 00:06:01,760
You think
I was all emotional yesterday?

192
00:06:01,760 --> 00:06:04,240
I did calm down
and think it through rationally.

193
00:06:05,080 --> 00:06:07,080
You spent an hour and a half driving back,

194
00:06:07,080 --> 00:06:08,440
and I spent that whole time

195
00:06:08,440 --> 00:06:09,440
thinking, too.

196
00:06:09,520 --> 00:06:10,320
Alright, I get it.

197
00:06:28,720 --> 00:06:30,880
Since we're both so cautious

198
00:06:30,880 --> 00:06:31,750
and torn up about it

199
00:06:33,840 --> 00:06:34,640
before it starts,

200
00:06:34,640 --> 00:06:36,040
we're imagining the worst outcome.

201
00:06:36,040 --> 00:06:37,130
What's the point of trying?

202
00:06:38,640 --> 00:06:40,120
Right?

203
00:06:43,520 --> 00:06:44,320
It's like hiking.

204
00:06:44,320 --> 00:06:46,560
You start climbing from the bottom
step by step.

205
00:06:46,560 --> 00:06:47,640
Halfway up, you rest.

206
00:06:47,640 --> 00:06:49,000
Then you think about pushing on.

207
00:06:49,080 --> 00:06:50,160
Or at the foot,

208
00:06:50,160 --> 00:06:51,240
you see it's way too high.

209
00:06:51,240 --> 00:06:52,040
And decide not to go

210
00:06:52,760 --> 00:06:53,720
and head home.

211
00:06:59,760 --> 00:07:02,080
I've already made my position clear.

212
00:07:02,080 --> 00:07:03,680
I've told you exactly what I think.

213
00:07:03,680 --> 00:07:06,040
So why are you still

214
00:07:06,040 --> 00:07:07,760
hesitating about this?

215
00:07:08,600 --> 00:07:10,320
I really can't get him anymore.

216
00:07:10,440 --> 00:07:11,440
He's different every day.

217
00:07:12,080 --> 00:07:13,520
Not sure if yesterday's script

218
00:07:13,520 --> 00:07:15,320
had some effect on him.

219
00:07:25,680 --> 00:07:27,840
Look, here's what I said.

220
00:07:27,840 --> 00:07:30,240
I said with the long-distance thing,

221
00:07:30,680 --> 00:07:32,280
there are plenty of ways to make it work.

222
00:07:32,840 --> 00:07:35,360
So tell me,
wouldn't that feel strange to you?

223
00:07:35,360 --> 00:07:36,800
Right. I know I was wrong.

224
00:07:36,800 --> 00:07:38,920
Sometimes I talk too much.

225
00:07:39,520 --> 00:07:41,840
It made you misunderstand.

226
00:07:51,850 --> 00:07:52,960
That idea you had last night

227
00:07:52,960 --> 00:07:53,960
almost made me

228
00:07:54,440 --> 00:07:57,000
trip down the steps.

229
00:07:59,480 --> 00:08:01,720
Why can't you just listen?

230
00:08:04,520 --> 00:08:05,720
I'm just not that quick-minded.

231
00:08:05,720 --> 00:08:07,040
And I tend to overthink.

232
00:08:07,360 --> 00:08:08,400
I think about the motive

233
00:08:08,520 --> 00:08:10,720
behind what you're saying.

234
00:08:15,000 --> 00:08:17,840
We often get stuck on certain points.

235
00:08:17,840 --> 00:08:20,120
It's like we keep seeing things
from each other's view.

236
00:08:20,120 --> 00:08:22,640
But never really figure out
what's on each other's mind.

237
00:08:23,360 --> 00:08:24,930
Ending on the island is the same.

238
00:08:24,990 --> 00:08:26,620
Off the island is where it really begins.

239
00:08:26,840 --> 00:08:28,880
It's like a special episode in a TV drama.

240
00:08:29,200 --> 00:08:30,840
You have an ending in the TV drama.

241
00:08:30,840 --> 00:08:31,800
But after it ends,

242
00:08:31,800 --> 00:08:32,840
if it's supposed to go on,

243
00:08:32,840 --> 00:08:33,400
we'd need more

244
00:08:33,420 --> 00:08:34,360
like a special episode.

245
00:08:35,160 --> 00:08:37,280
A special episode would mean a fresh start,

246
00:08:39,800 --> 00:08:40,600
right?

247
00:08:43,580 --> 00:08:44,480
Does that make sense?

248
00:08:44,480 --> 00:08:45,120
Yeah.

249
00:08:46,560 --> 00:08:48,360
Everyone says we should follow Yang's lead.

250
00:08:48,360 --> 00:08:49,920
I agree with Yang on that.

251
00:08:55,240 --> 00:08:56,680
Let's go.

252
00:08:56,680 --> 00:08:58,960
Or we'll be staying too long.

253
00:09:01,680 --> 00:09:03,000
I was sure about my decision,

254
00:09:03,000 --> 00:09:05,160
but I don't know what Enda is thinking.

255
00:09:05,360 --> 00:09:07,680
We've talked a lot,

256
00:09:07,800 --> 00:09:08,520
but never reached

257
00:09:08,520 --> 00:09:10,560
any clear

258
00:09:11,120 --> 00:09:12,200
conclusion.

259
00:09:13,080 --> 00:09:14,360
It's more like,

260
00:09:15,000 --> 00:09:17,040
we just kind of reached
a mutual understanding.

261
00:09:18,980 --> 00:09:19,480
Where's Yan?

262
00:09:19,500 --> 00:09:20,440
Yan already left.

263
00:09:21,600 --> 00:09:23,360
Everyone went out to buy gifts.

264
00:09:26,960 --> 00:09:28,280
Picking gifts is hard.

265
00:09:29,000 --> 00:09:30,240
Birthdays are easy,

266
00:09:30,240 --> 00:09:32,200
but confessing to a guy?

267
00:09:32,200 --> 00:09:34,320
This is literally a first for me.

268
00:09:34,680 --> 00:09:35,760
I'm losing my mind.

269
00:09:36,640 --> 00:09:40,120
It's my first time confessing to a guy.

270
00:09:42,680 --> 00:09:43,920
Maybe I should buy him a ring.

271
00:09:43,920 --> 00:09:45,960
And go straight to marriage.

272
00:09:46,840 --> 00:09:52,520
Off to get Yan a keepsake.

273
00:09:52,520 --> 00:09:53,120
Go, go.

274
00:09:53,120 --> 00:09:54,040
He's probably

275
00:09:54,040 --> 00:09:55,760
getting a gift for me too.

276
00:09:56,040 --> 00:09:57,040
His confession gift.

277
00:09:57,160 --> 00:09:59,600
I can't wait to see what he's prepared.

278
00:09:59,620 --> 00:10:01,620
(The gift is on its way...)

279
00:10:05,600 --> 00:10:07,120
A girl who loves

280
00:10:07,240 --> 00:10:08,320
preparing gifts.

281
00:10:08,360 --> 00:10:08,840
I really

282
00:10:08,840 --> 00:10:10,080
enjoy that feeling

283
00:10:10,080 --> 00:10:12,840
of preparing gifts for someone.

284
00:10:14,640 --> 00:10:16,360
These are so cute.

285
00:10:16,360 --> 00:10:19,240
The time before confessing my feelings

286
00:10:19,240 --> 00:10:21,760
is actually the hardest part.

287
00:10:22,200 --> 00:10:23,560
It's like waiting for an exam.

288
00:10:24,710 --> 00:10:26,550
The closer it gets,
the more nervous you are.

289
00:10:26,800 --> 00:10:28,120
Even if you're the top student,

290
00:10:28,120 --> 00:10:29,760
and you've practiced every question,

291
00:10:30,280 --> 00:10:32,040
what if there's one question

292
00:10:32,040 --> 00:10:34,320
you've never seen before?

293
00:10:39,600 --> 00:10:40,520
Which one looks better?

294
00:10:41,810 --> 00:10:43,440
Maybe I'll just buy a few.

295
00:10:43,440 --> 00:10:44,400
Safer that way.

296
00:10:44,430 --> 00:10:45,560
But I don't know if they have

297
00:10:45,560 --> 00:10:47,280
sheep-themed pendants,

298
00:10:47,280 --> 00:10:48,080
or little figurines,

299
00:10:48,080 --> 00:10:49,560
or other small items like that.

300
00:10:49,920 --> 00:10:51,240
I can't exactly buy a ram's horn.

301
00:10:51,240 --> 00:10:52,240
That doesn't sound right.

302
00:10:52,240 --> 00:10:53,520
Buy him some lamb.

303
00:10:53,640 --> 00:10:55,040
He loves lamb kidney.

304
00:10:55,040 --> 00:10:56,040
Or other kinds of offal.

305
00:10:56,480 --> 00:10:58,080
But that's not really romantic.

306
00:10:58,280 --> 00:10:59,320
(My heart and liver)
Here are your insides.

307
00:10:59,320 --> 00:11:00,440
Want me to cook it for you?

308
00:11:00,440 --> 00:11:01,640
Feels a bit wrong again.

309
00:11:01,640 --> 00:11:02,480
A basketball maybe.

310
00:11:02,480 --> 00:11:03,960
But that's still off.

311
00:11:03,960 --> 00:11:04,720
He's into gaming.

312
00:11:04,720 --> 00:11:06,480
I can't buy him a game.

313
00:11:06,480 --> 00:11:07,680
He'd play nonstop and

314
00:11:07,680 --> 00:11:08,390
forget about me.

315
00:11:08,400 --> 00:11:08,880
No way.

316
00:11:08,880 --> 00:11:10,480
Maybe I should give him sneakers.

317
00:11:10,480 --> 00:11:12,320
No, they say gifting shoes is bad luck.

318
00:11:12,320 --> 00:11:14,640
What if I just give him a red envelope,
wish him success

319
00:11:14,640 --> 00:11:16,520
and a happy new year?

320
00:11:17,200 --> 00:11:19,400
What am I thinking?

321
00:11:19,400 --> 00:11:20,760
Buying gifts for men is hard.

322
00:11:20,760 --> 00:11:21,800
They're so hard to read.

323
00:11:22,600 --> 00:11:23,400
Sir.

324
00:11:23,960 --> 00:11:24,920
Excuse me, sir.

325
00:11:25,440 --> 00:11:27,440
When someone confesses to you,

326
00:11:27,440 --> 00:11:28,920
what gift would you like?

327
00:11:29,240 --> 00:11:31,960
If you're into them, anything works.

328
00:11:32,520 --> 00:11:34,120
If you're not, nothing helps.

329
00:11:34,260 --> 00:11:38,340
(Running low on energy...)

330
00:11:39,720 --> 00:11:40,520
I'm the unluckiest.

331
00:11:40,520 --> 00:11:41,480
2nd time off the island.

332
00:11:42,120 --> 00:11:43,560
I'm fine. Fourth time.

333
00:11:45,360 --> 00:11:46,720
You guys are lucky enough.

334
00:11:47,560 --> 00:11:48,440
Not really.

335
00:11:49,800 --> 00:11:51,080
We may not have found happiness,

336
00:11:51,080 --> 00:11:52,640
but the journey was full of it.

337
00:11:53,440 --> 00:11:54,480
Happy times.

338
00:11:54,480 --> 00:11:55,580
(Envy written all over my face)

339
00:11:55,660 --> 00:11:58,660
(This guy too)

340
00:11:58,680 --> 00:12:00,040
You two didn't sleep well?

341
00:12:01,000 --> 00:12:01,740
I stayed up late.

342
00:12:01,790 --> 00:12:02,640
He went to bed first.

343
00:12:03,200 --> 00:12:04,600
You could even sleep?

344
00:12:06,760 --> 00:12:07,880
He slept like a baby.

345
00:12:10,080 --> 00:12:11,380
Guess the feelings aren't strong.

346
00:12:12,280 --> 00:12:13,240
Not strong enough?

347
00:12:13,240 --> 00:12:14,040
For who?

348
00:12:14,780 --> 00:12:16,070
(Slept early, slept poorly.)
The village chief.

349
00:12:17,760 --> 00:12:19,000
Lu, any thoughts?

350
00:12:19,000 --> 00:12:19,560
Me?

351
00:12:19,560 --> 00:12:20,480
Life is

352
00:12:20,480 --> 00:12:21,280
full of flavors.

353
00:12:21,280 --> 00:12:22,000
Really...

354
00:12:22,520 --> 00:12:23,600
My first time in life...

355
00:12:23,600 --> 00:12:24,420
Experienced so much.

356
00:12:24,480 --> 00:12:25,200
I learned a lot.

357
00:12:25,200 --> 00:12:26,080
Really learned a lot.

358
00:12:26,440 --> 00:12:27,560
Maybe not that much.

359
00:12:27,560 --> 00:12:28,720
But you learned to cook.

360
00:12:28,720 --> 00:12:29,800
(Savage bro moment)

361
00:12:29,800 --> 00:12:31,000
You've learned how to cook.

362
00:12:31,520 --> 00:12:32,840
From now on, you're Chef Lu.

363
00:12:33,080 --> 00:12:33,760
Chef Lu.

364
00:12:33,760 --> 00:12:34,840
(Chef Lu is off duty today...)

365
00:12:34,840 --> 00:12:36,320
Yeah, just... regrets.

366
00:12:36,320 --> 00:12:37,240
I do feel regretful.

367
00:12:37,240 --> 00:12:38,600
(A little regretful)

368
00:12:38,600 --> 00:12:39,960
But I'm not saying I'm, like,

369
00:12:40,960 --> 00:12:41,960
entirely unhappy.

370
00:12:47,120 --> 00:12:47,920
A little bee.

371
00:12:47,920 --> 00:12:51,060
(A little bee)

372
00:12:51,080 --> 00:12:52,560
Let little bee fly away.

373
00:12:53,040 --> 00:12:54,480
Go on, little bee.

374
00:12:54,480 --> 00:12:55,440
(What's going on?)

375
00:12:55,440 --> 00:12:58,880
Go on.

376
00:12:59,560 --> 00:13:02,000
Go find the other half in life.

377
00:13:03,800 --> 00:13:04,920
What are you doing?

378
00:13:04,920 --> 00:13:06,480
Why are you still hanging around?

379
00:13:07,240 --> 00:13:08,240
The little bee.

380
00:13:08,840 --> 00:13:10,160
Stubborn, just like me.

381
00:13:10,400 --> 00:13:11,480
Exactly like you.

382
00:13:12,080 --> 00:13:14,840
Running into a wall and still pushing.

383
00:13:15,040 --> 00:13:16,760
Won't turn back even if it hits a dead end.

384
00:13:20,160 --> 00:13:22,080
Go on.

385
00:13:22,680 --> 00:13:23,480
Just leave it be.

386
00:13:23,480 --> 00:13:24,720
It'll fly off in a bit.

387
00:13:33,520 --> 00:13:35,240
Where do you think someone goes to confess?

388
00:13:35,400 --> 00:13:36,640
Why are you thinking about them?

389
00:13:37,600 --> 00:13:38,240
Just...

390
00:13:39,040 --> 00:13:39,920
Tonight's confessions

391
00:13:39,920 --> 00:13:41,920
gotta be at somewhere special, right?

392
00:13:42,400 --> 00:13:43,440
Tonight we'll sit together.

393
00:13:43,440 --> 00:13:44,680
Quietly.

394
00:13:44,680 --> 00:13:45,720
We can add some commentary.

395
00:13:45,720 --> 00:13:47,520
Taking it all in.

396
00:13:47,800 --> 00:13:48,760
I won't take it in.

397
00:13:48,760 --> 00:13:49,520
That's all you.

398
00:13:49,520 --> 00:13:50,320
Just saying.

399
00:13:50,320 --> 00:13:51,440
(No shoulder to cry on. Don't make a scene.)

400
00:13:51,440 --> 00:13:52,960
Thanks a lot.

401
00:13:53,480 --> 00:13:55,120
Honestly, I'm pretty curious

402
00:13:55,120 --> 00:13:56,880
to see your face when the time comes.

403
00:13:57,400 --> 00:13:58,360
Your expression.

404
00:13:58,360 --> 00:14:00,480
You'll definitely be like,

405
00:14:00,480 --> 00:14:02,320
"If only that was me up there."

406
00:14:03,480 --> 00:14:04,920
That's how I feel right now.

407
00:14:06,800 --> 00:14:07,480
Right?

408
00:14:09,920 --> 00:14:10,720
I'm full.

409
00:14:11,160 --> 00:14:11,840
Let's go.

410
00:14:12,320 --> 00:14:14,400
Heading home for the very last time.

411
00:14:14,640 --> 00:14:16,400
The very last trip home.

412
00:14:18,000 --> 00:14:20,080
Feels like I don't want to leave.

413
00:14:23,000 --> 00:14:24,000
Going home.

414
00:14:25,600 --> 00:14:27,440
Why is the weather gloomy too?

415
00:14:28,080 --> 00:14:29,280
This really hurts.

416
00:14:29,880 --> 00:14:31,240
Definitely gonna miss this place.

417
00:14:34,700 --> 00:14:39,020
(Countdown to the Final Confession)

418
00:14:43,160 --> 00:14:43,960
Hello.

419
00:14:43,960 --> 00:14:44,840
Hello.

420
00:14:45,160 --> 00:14:46,360
Wow, this is quite a feast.

421
00:14:46,360 --> 00:14:47,240
Yeah.

422
00:14:47,240 --> 00:14:48,160
Our last meal together.

423
00:14:49,800 --> 00:14:51,480
This looks delicious.

424
00:14:54,000 --> 00:14:56,160
Come on, I've got some gifts for you.

425
00:14:56,400 --> 00:14:57,360
Here, for the girls.

426
00:14:57,360 --> 00:14:57,920
Ladies, here.

427
00:14:57,920 --> 00:14:59,320
Thanks.

428
00:14:59,680 --> 00:15:00,680
Thank you, village chief.

429
00:15:00,680 --> 00:15:02,920
I hope you girls shine like a snow globe.

430
00:15:02,920 --> 00:15:03,680
It'll surround you

431
00:15:03,680 --> 00:15:05,160
and keep you safe, okay?

432
00:15:06,880 --> 00:15:08,280
Did you rehearse that speech?

433
00:15:08,280 --> 00:15:10,000
For the guys, wishing bottles.

434
00:15:10,000 --> 00:15:11,640
I hope all your wishes come true.

435
00:15:11,640 --> 00:15:12,600
Thanks.

436
00:15:13,400 --> 00:15:14,680
Wanning.

437
00:15:16,160 --> 00:15:17,200
Thank you.

438
00:15:18,200 --> 00:15:19,160
That's thoughtful.

439
00:15:19,160 --> 00:15:20,480
You even wrote a letter.

440
00:15:24,320 --> 00:15:25,240
Yijia.

441
00:15:25,240 --> 00:15:26,160
This is so touching.

442
00:15:26,160 --> 00:15:27,480
It actually made me tear up.

443
00:15:27,480 --> 00:15:28,600
Really?

444
00:15:28,600 --> 00:15:30,280
Yes, it's so moving.

445
00:15:30,280 --> 00:15:31,720
My dear.

446
00:15:34,760 --> 00:15:36,680
Yijia gave me a letter.

447
00:15:37,080 --> 00:15:38,040
It's just words

448
00:15:38,040 --> 00:15:39,600
from a sis to her big bro.

449
00:15:40,120 --> 00:15:42,480
(Chen Yijia writes letters for everyone.)
I was honestly super moved.

450
00:15:42,720 --> 00:15:44,720
(Bro, lucky to have you looking out for me.)
I'm honored to have her as my sister.

451
00:15:45,180 --> 00:15:48,220
(Wanning, confident and mature...
the highest praise I can give.)

452
00:15:48,220 --> 00:15:49,140
(Yang, talking with you is so easy.
I love your sharp mind. Let's hang out more.)

453
00:15:49,140 --> 00:15:49,940
(Charlie, from day one you surprised me.
You showed me humor's attractive.)

454
00:15:49,940 --> 00:15:51,040
(Jiayi, thanks for helping me
and staying by my side.)

455
00:15:51,040 --> 00:15:51,760
(Enda, I got you two a pair of bunnies.)
Yijia.

456
00:15:52,200 --> 00:15:53,240
This one's for you.

457
00:15:53,240 --> 00:15:54,480
I think you're really smart.

458
00:15:54,480 --> 00:15:56,240
You're like a top student.

459
00:15:56,240 --> 00:15:57,150
Always in the library.

460
00:15:57,160 --> 00:15:57,680
Thanks.

461
00:15:57,680 --> 00:16:00,360
And I hope you stay in one piece

462
00:16:00,360 --> 00:16:01,720
and be happy like a puppy.

463
00:16:01,720 --> 00:16:03,320
Alright, thank you.

464
00:16:03,480 --> 00:16:04,480
This is adorable.

465
00:16:04,480 --> 00:16:05,080
Super cute.

466
00:16:05,080 --> 00:16:06,240
He built it.

467
00:16:06,240 --> 00:16:07,280
Seriously, you built it?

468
00:16:07,280 --> 00:16:08,360
Built it himself.

469
00:16:08,560 --> 00:16:09,560
Guys.

470
00:16:10,240 --> 00:16:11,560
I got something for you.

471
00:16:12,120 --> 00:16:13,120
Okay.

472
00:16:13,440 --> 00:16:14,720
For the girls, I bought you

473
00:16:14,720 --> 00:16:16,520
lipsticks in different shades.

474
00:16:16,520 --> 00:16:17,440
And this one's for Yan.

475
00:16:17,440 --> 00:16:19,040
Thanks, sweetheart.

476
00:16:19,120 --> 00:16:21,080
Inside, there are building blocks.

477
00:16:21,080 --> 00:16:21,600
So...

478
00:16:21,880 --> 00:16:24,240
I think you guys will totally love this.

479
00:16:24,360 --> 00:16:26,720
Hope you can keep that childlike joy.

480
00:16:26,720 --> 00:16:29,520
And let me explain.

481
00:16:33,640 --> 00:16:35,120
This lobster.

482
00:16:35,120 --> 00:16:37,040
I found it hilarious when I first saw it.

483
00:16:37,040 --> 00:16:38,560
Because we're on the island.

484
00:16:38,560 --> 00:16:40,840
Thought we could bring
some seafood back as a souvenir.

485
00:16:41,040 --> 00:16:42,880
But on the ride back,

486
00:16:42,880 --> 00:16:43,880
Yijia reminded me

487
00:16:43,880 --> 00:16:45,320
that lobster carries another meaning.

488
00:16:45,320 --> 00:16:46,720
I think that's awesome.

489
00:16:46,960 --> 00:16:48,320
Lobsters are creatures

490
00:16:48,320 --> 00:16:50,240
known for being devoted and loyal.

491
00:16:50,240 --> 00:16:52,440
They're monogamous.

492
00:16:52,440 --> 00:16:55,440
So here's to everyone finding the one.

493
00:16:57,040 --> 00:16:59,640
And may our friendship last forever.

494
00:16:59,640 --> 00:17:00,680
Yes.

495
00:17:00,680 --> 00:17:01,440
For sure.

496
00:17:01,440 --> 00:17:02,400
Thanks.

497
00:17:03,200 --> 00:17:04,480
Okay, let's sit down

498
00:17:04,480 --> 00:17:06,440
and enjoy our last meal on the island.

499
00:17:06,440 --> 00:17:07,240
Sounds good.

500
00:17:07,560 --> 00:17:08,840
Let's do it.

501
00:17:11,840 --> 00:17:12,720
Do you eat vegetables?

502
00:17:12,720 --> 00:17:13,200
Yeah.

503
00:17:13,200 --> 00:17:13,900
Have some more.

504
00:17:14,560 --> 00:17:14,960
Thanks.

505
00:17:14,960 --> 00:17:16,480
Thanks, babe.

506
00:17:16,480 --> 00:17:17,240
I love you.

507
00:17:17,360 --> 00:17:18,120
Love you too.

508
00:17:18,120 --> 00:17:20,280
What am I supposed to do now?

509
00:17:20,280 --> 00:17:21,440
You're taking my job away.

510
00:17:23,360 --> 00:17:25,240
I just want you to have good food.

511
00:17:25,240 --> 00:17:26,360
Thank you.

512
00:17:26,360 --> 00:17:27,050
Spotted it.

513
00:17:27,060 --> 00:17:27,880
Thanks.

514
00:17:28,480 --> 00:17:29,440
And you say...

515
00:17:30,240 --> 00:17:30,960
Say it.

516
00:17:30,960 --> 00:17:31,280
Thanks.

517
00:17:33,640 --> 00:17:34,960
Do you want me to say it here?

518
00:17:34,960 --> 00:17:36,040
Yeah, like yesterday.

519
00:17:36,040 --> 00:17:36,800
You've lost it.

520
00:17:36,880 --> 00:17:37,800
Go on, say it.

521
00:17:37,920 --> 00:17:39,040
Thanks, honey.

522
00:17:39,040 --> 00:17:40,040
You're welcome.

523
00:17:43,240 --> 00:17:44,760
You woke up acting like a stranger.

524
00:17:48,660 --> 00:17:50,180
(Turning sadness into appetite)

525
00:17:50,480 --> 00:17:51,720
I got one for you too.

526
00:17:52,560 --> 00:17:55,120
It's a gift with a special meaning.

527
00:17:55,120 --> 00:17:56,000
A meaningful gift?

528
00:17:56,000 --> 00:17:56,440
Right.

529
00:17:56,720 --> 00:17:58,360
You set the bar so high for everyone.

530
00:17:58,360 --> 00:18:00,040
No diamond ring,

531
00:18:00,040 --> 00:18:00,920
and you'll lose face.

532
00:18:03,600 --> 00:18:04,790
An engagement ring's too much.

533
00:18:04,810 --> 00:18:06,400
We aren't even dating yet.

534
00:18:06,920 --> 00:18:07,800
I'll show you later.

535
00:18:10,600 --> 00:18:11,400
Keeping me guessing.

536
00:18:17,320 --> 00:18:18,200
Do you want some?

537
00:18:18,200 --> 00:18:19,200
I could take one bite.

538
00:18:22,360 --> 00:18:23,160
Sweet, right?

539
00:18:24,040 --> 00:18:25,040
Are you hooked?

540
00:18:25,040 --> 00:18:25,920
You're sweeter though.

541
00:18:28,640 --> 00:18:29,440
What's this?

542
00:18:30,560 --> 00:18:31,240
What kind?

543
00:18:31,240 --> 00:18:31,920
No idea.

544
00:18:31,920 --> 00:18:33,000
But it's delicious.

545
00:18:40,160 --> 00:18:42,120
Keep it together later.

546
00:18:42,200 --> 00:18:42,920
Just don't cry.

547
00:18:42,940 --> 00:18:44,240
If you cry, I'll cry too.

548
00:18:44,520 --> 00:18:45,680
I've been practicing this

549
00:18:45,680 --> 00:18:47,040
in the mirror.

550
00:18:47,040 --> 00:18:48,600
I hope it moves you.

551
00:18:51,760 --> 00:18:53,520
You don't need to go all out.

552
00:18:55,510 --> 00:18:56,960
What? Is there a subtext here?

553
00:19:00,800 --> 00:19:01,920
Come on, let's toast.

554
00:19:01,920 --> 00:19:02,480
Sure.

555
00:19:02,480 --> 00:19:03,040
Sure.

556
00:19:03,520 --> 00:19:05,440
From when we barely knew each other,

557
00:19:05,840 --> 00:19:08,840
to now, really knowing each other.

558
00:19:08,840 --> 00:19:09,720
Some even found love.

559
00:19:09,920 --> 00:19:12,200
Once we leave the island

560
00:19:12,200 --> 00:19:14,960
and head back to the real world,
I hope nothing changes.

561
00:19:14,960 --> 00:19:16,360
Friends for life.

562
00:19:16,360 --> 00:19:17,960
Just like it was on Balance Island.

563
00:19:17,960 --> 00:19:18,240
Yeah.

564
00:19:18,240 --> 00:19:19,120
Absolutely.

565
00:19:19,120 --> 00:19:20,960
Come on.

566
00:19:25,520 --> 00:19:27,040
This is our last meal on the island.

567
00:19:27,240 --> 00:19:28,680
Anyone want to say something?

568
00:19:30,920 --> 00:19:32,320
I'll go first.

569
00:19:33,160 --> 00:19:36,600
I was the first to arrive on the island.

570
00:19:36,800 --> 00:19:38,720
On my first day, I barely spoke.

571
00:19:38,960 --> 00:19:40,520
I didn't know how to break the ice

572
00:19:40,520 --> 00:19:42,120
or what to talk about.

573
00:19:42,840 --> 00:19:43,640
Honestly,

574
00:19:43,640 --> 00:19:46,360
I never expected to gain so much here

575
00:19:46,360 --> 00:19:47,840
and have such a great time.

576
00:19:48,720 --> 00:19:51,000
I feel like on this island,

577
00:19:51,000 --> 00:19:53,200
I'm the happiest person here.

578
00:19:53,560 --> 00:19:54,480
I've felt

579
00:19:54,480 --> 00:19:56,440
so much warmth and kindness,

580
00:19:56,440 --> 00:19:57,320
and genuine care.

581
00:19:57,720 --> 00:19:59,760
And I especially want

582
00:19:59,760 --> 00:20:00,720
to thank Yanting.

583
00:20:06,920 --> 00:20:09,160
You made me breakfast

584
00:20:09,160 --> 00:20:10,920
and even picked flowers for me.

585
00:20:11,920 --> 00:20:13,960
I never imagined

586
00:20:13,960 --> 00:20:16,520
I'd receive such beautiful bouquets

587
00:20:16,520 --> 00:20:19,520
on an island like this.

588
00:20:19,640 --> 00:20:21,720
It's honestly the most special gift

589
00:20:21,720 --> 00:20:23,640
and the most touching one I've ever had.

590
00:20:23,640 --> 00:20:24,440
Yeah.

591
00:20:25,400 --> 00:20:28,200
And I also want to say I'm sorry.

592
00:20:28,200 --> 00:20:30,720
Because honestly, I haven't really

593
00:20:30,960 --> 00:20:33,920
done much for you in return.

594
00:20:38,520 --> 00:20:41,320
There were moments

595
00:20:41,560 --> 00:20:44,320
where I was just avoiding things

596
00:20:44,520 --> 00:20:46,960
and my emotions.

597
00:20:48,040 --> 00:20:48,750
I'm sorry.

598
00:20:48,750 --> 00:20:50,580
♪Don't let it go♪

599
00:20:50,850 --> 00:20:52,780
♪We'll let it grow♪

600
00:20:52,780 --> 00:20:59,290
♪This could be whatever we want, want♪

601
00:20:59,560 --> 00:21:03,410
♪Whatever we want, want♪

602
00:21:03,560 --> 00:21:04,360
No.

603
00:21:04,360 --> 00:21:06,550
♪I need you to be solid♪

604
00:21:06,550 --> 00:21:07,840
♪Promise♪

605
00:21:07,920 --> 00:21:08,610
Hug it out.

606
00:21:10,160 --> 00:21:11,880
Thank you, really, thank you.

607
00:21:12,060 --> 00:21:16,890
♪I need you to be solid♪

608
00:21:17,220 --> 00:21:18,830
♪Promise♪

609
00:21:19,060 --> 00:21:22,660
♪That you won't bend or break♪

610
00:21:23,180 --> 00:21:28,500
♪Promise me you'll stay, baby♪

611
00:21:33,890 --> 00:21:35,080
Alright, let me share too.

612
00:21:35,080 --> 00:21:37,040
I feel that with Lu and me,

613
00:21:37,040 --> 00:21:40,000
we probably just can't

614
00:21:40,000 --> 00:21:41,840
truly ease this tension well.

615
00:21:41,840 --> 00:21:43,440
But I don't see that as a problem.

616
00:21:43,440 --> 00:21:45,320
It's because we simply can't.

617
00:21:45,320 --> 00:21:46,840
We both liked the same girl.

618
00:21:47,240 --> 00:21:48,720
But when it comes to you,

619
00:21:48,720 --> 00:21:50,560
there's so much I can learn from.

620
00:21:51,120 --> 00:21:51,760
No matter what.

621
00:21:51,760 --> 00:21:52,560
What happens here

622
00:21:52,560 --> 00:21:53,400
stays here.

623
00:21:54,160 --> 00:21:56,040
We can still be friends after this.

624
00:21:56,040 --> 00:21:56,480
Right.

625
00:21:56,480 --> 00:21:58,000
No matter who Jiayi chooses.

626
00:21:58,000 --> 00:21:59,320
Or if she chooses no one at all.

627
00:21:59,520 --> 00:22:02,560
We just want her to be happy.

628
00:22:02,640 --> 00:22:03,440
Yes.

629
00:22:04,720 --> 00:22:06,280
I feel the same way.

630
00:22:06,280 --> 00:22:07,520
To respond to Charlie.

631
00:22:08,760 --> 00:22:12,240
This is the first time
I've been in this situation.

632
00:22:12,440 --> 00:22:17,680
Competing with another guy for the same girl.

633
00:22:17,960 --> 00:22:20,200
I think we've both given

634
00:22:20,200 --> 00:22:22,080
each other plenty of space

635
00:22:22,080 --> 00:22:22,920
and respect.

636
00:22:22,920 --> 00:22:23,200
Yes.

637
00:22:23,200 --> 00:22:24,480
Because we both understood

638
00:22:24,480 --> 00:22:26,440
that we didn't want
to put any pressure on Jiayi.

639
00:22:26,440 --> 00:22:27,240
Yes.

640
00:22:27,240 --> 00:22:28,760
In that sense,

641
00:22:28,760 --> 00:22:32,920
I think we should stay in touch after this.

642
00:22:33,440 --> 00:22:34,240
Really.

643
00:22:38,120 --> 00:22:41,560
I also want to thank Jiayi.

644
00:22:42,440 --> 00:22:44,760
You kept telling me all along,

645
00:22:44,760 --> 00:22:45,920
just be yourself,

646
00:22:46,480 --> 00:22:47,720
don't overthink it.

647
00:22:48,720 --> 00:22:50,920
Before this, I kept pushing myself

648
00:22:50,920 --> 00:22:53,440
to control my emotions with logic.

649
00:22:53,840 --> 00:22:56,880
But Jiayi made me realize,

650
00:22:56,960 --> 00:23:00,840
sometimes you need to let your feelings out.

651
00:23:01,440 --> 00:23:03,040
So thank you, Jiayi.

652
00:23:09,720 --> 00:23:11,440
Okay, my turn.

653
00:23:12,480 --> 00:23:14,440
For me,

654
00:23:14,440 --> 00:23:16,080
the biggest thing I've gained is

655
00:23:16,240 --> 00:23:19,040
learning how to just be my true self here.

656
00:23:19,360 --> 00:23:21,080
When people first met me,

657
00:23:21,080 --> 00:23:23,680
they probably thought I was quiet,

658
00:23:23,680 --> 00:23:25,960
or maybe even a bit pretentious.

659
00:23:26,920 --> 00:23:29,120
And when I first arrived on the island,

660
00:23:29,120 --> 00:23:30,840
I was so nervous before coming here.

661
00:23:31,360 --> 00:23:34,640
I've never been a social butterfly.

662
00:23:34,920 --> 00:23:36,240
So during the first few days,

663
00:23:36,240 --> 00:23:38,160
I kept trying to present this

664
00:23:38,160 --> 00:23:39,480
"perfect" version of myself.

665
00:23:40,640 --> 00:23:43,920
But after spending time with you,

666
00:23:44,080 --> 00:23:45,960
I felt your energy and warmth.

667
00:23:45,960 --> 00:23:48,640
Everyone was so good to me.

668
00:23:48,920 --> 00:23:51,280
Slowly, the real me started coming out.

669
00:23:51,470 --> 00:23:53,360
(At dinner on Day 5)
I felt totally relaxed.

670
00:23:53,360 --> 00:23:54,240
I just let myself go.

671
00:23:54,240 --> 00:23:55,920
Come on, mimic her real quick.

672
00:23:55,920 --> 00:23:58,420
(Two nights ago)

673
00:23:58,440 --> 00:23:59,560
Wu Yihan, I never did that.

674
00:24:02,880 --> 00:24:06,840
And I really want to thank a few people.

675
00:24:06,840 --> 00:24:09,240
First, my roommate, Yang.

676
00:24:09,680 --> 00:24:10,680
Because she's the one

677
00:24:11,800 --> 00:24:14,120
who chats with me every night.

678
00:24:14,120 --> 00:24:16,280
She was the first person to reach out

679
00:24:16,280 --> 00:24:17,440
and see the real me.

680
00:24:18,120 --> 00:24:21,440
And I'd like to thank

681
00:24:21,440 --> 00:24:22,240
the village chief.

682
00:24:22,720 --> 00:24:24,640
We had our ups and downs

683
00:24:24,640 --> 00:24:25,840
since day one,

684
00:24:25,880 --> 00:24:27,360
but we talked it through.

685
00:24:27,360 --> 00:24:29,720
I just hope that no matter what happens,

686
00:24:29,720 --> 00:24:34,440
we can still be good friends.

687
00:24:34,520 --> 00:24:35,320
Yeah.

688
00:24:35,840 --> 00:24:38,840
And finally, you, Guanjie.

689
00:24:39,040 --> 00:24:40,040
You.

690
00:24:41,440 --> 00:24:42,770
Yes, you.

691
00:24:42,870 --> 00:24:44,120
What did you call him yesterday?

692
00:24:50,280 --> 00:24:51,640
What did you call him 100 times?

693
00:24:51,640 --> 00:24:52,960
A hundred times?

694
00:24:52,960 --> 00:24:54,920
You'll find out later.

695
00:24:54,920 --> 00:24:55,680
Well...

696
00:24:57,240 --> 00:24:58,760
I actually have a lot to say.

697
00:24:58,760 --> 00:24:59,760
Saving it for tonight.

698
00:24:59,760 --> 00:25:00,840
Just a teaser for now.

699
00:25:00,840 --> 00:25:02,440
I think you're a really shy person.

700
00:25:02,680 --> 00:25:04,240
Actually, before coming on the island,

701
00:25:04,640 --> 00:25:06,320
I never thought I'd meet

702
00:25:06,880 --> 00:25:09,760
someone I actually really like.

703
00:25:10,440 --> 00:25:13,840
Alright, I'll give a little spoiler.

704
00:25:13,840 --> 00:25:15,840
Okay then.

705
00:25:15,840 --> 00:25:17,520
Anyway, I'll share more about it later.

706
00:25:19,400 --> 00:25:20,640
Hope you're less shy next time.

707
00:25:20,640 --> 00:25:21,240
Alright.

708
00:25:21,640 --> 00:25:23,040
Okay, I'm done.

709
00:25:28,160 --> 00:25:29,680
My turn, I guess.

710
00:25:29,840 --> 00:25:30,960
Well...

711
00:25:31,480 --> 00:25:34,440
I feel like these past few days,

712
00:25:34,440 --> 00:25:36,960
I haven't spent that much time

713
00:25:36,960 --> 00:25:38,360
with everyone.

714
00:25:38,360 --> 00:25:40,280
Because I've mostly been hanging with

715
00:25:40,720 --> 00:25:42,120
with one guy, just talking.

716
00:25:42,120 --> 00:25:43,280
(That guy)
Hoping to figure something out.

717
00:25:43,480 --> 00:25:44,760
But honestly,

718
00:25:44,760 --> 00:25:46,120
when I first came on the island,

719
00:25:46,120 --> 00:25:47,320
I had no expectations.

720
00:25:47,320 --> 00:25:49,320
I wasn't planning to start a romance here.

721
00:25:49,320 --> 00:25:50,760
Or maybe something has to happen.

722
00:25:50,760 --> 00:25:53,640
I came here just to experience it.

723
00:25:54,280 --> 00:25:57,240
And I kept an open mind.

724
00:25:57,240 --> 00:25:58,520
To receive

725
00:25:58,520 --> 00:26:00,760
everyone's light

726
00:26:00,760 --> 00:26:01,480
and energy.

727
00:26:01,480 --> 00:26:03,880
The way each of you approaches life

728
00:26:03,880 --> 00:26:05,240
and love

729
00:26:05,240 --> 00:26:06,640
really inspired me.

730
00:26:06,840 --> 00:26:09,560
Everyone expresses love differently.

731
00:26:09,640 --> 00:26:11,160
Some are deeply passionate.

732
00:26:11,840 --> 00:26:13,160
Some are gentle and delicate.

733
00:26:13,920 --> 00:26:15,440
Some love boldly and fiercely.

734
00:26:15,440 --> 00:26:16,760
Once decided, they move forward.

735
00:26:16,920 --> 00:26:18,040
I think every style of love

736
00:26:18,040 --> 00:26:21,040
has quietly influenced me

737
00:26:21,360 --> 00:26:23,520
and made me rediscover myself.

738
00:26:24,720 --> 00:26:26,760
In these final days,

739
00:26:26,760 --> 00:26:28,440
I've been thinking seriously

740
00:26:28,440 --> 00:26:30,240
about starting a new relationship.

741
00:26:30,560 --> 00:26:32,720
Thank you Hanhan for setting up

742
00:26:32,840 --> 00:26:34,280
that date for us yesterday.

743
00:26:34,360 --> 00:26:36,560
It let me see deep into my own heart.

744
00:26:36,920 --> 00:26:38,720
And I feel this journey

745
00:26:38,720 --> 00:26:41,120
has helped me find
a whole new side of myself.

746
00:26:41,680 --> 00:26:44,440
I'm also thankful for your care and company.

747
00:26:44,640 --> 00:26:45,840
Love you all, thank you.

748
00:26:51,720 --> 00:26:53,720
Everyone's shared so much just now.

749
00:26:53,720 --> 00:26:54,640
But honestly,

750
00:26:54,640 --> 00:26:56,120
everything I want to say

751
00:26:56,120 --> 00:26:59,520
is already in those little envelopes.

752
00:26:59,720 --> 00:27:00,840
So, this next part

753
00:27:00,840 --> 00:27:02,640
is just for me.

754
00:27:03,120 --> 00:27:05,760
Still, let me reintroduce myself.

755
00:27:05,840 --> 00:27:07,040
Just like the first day.

756
00:27:07,320 --> 00:27:09,080
Hi everyone, I'm Chen Yijia.

757
00:27:09,080 --> 00:27:10,760
"Yijia" as in "one family."

758
00:27:10,760 --> 00:27:13,040
Glad to become family with you all.

759
00:27:15,160 --> 00:27:17,480
Before coming, I was scared
I'd have an allergic reaction.

760
00:27:17,880 --> 00:27:19,480
So I brought plenty of medicine.

761
00:27:19,840 --> 00:27:20,880
And I actually used it all.

762
00:27:20,880 --> 00:27:22,560
Because in my 11 days here,

763
00:27:22,560 --> 00:27:25,040
I spent 5 or 6 days dealing with allergies.

764
00:27:25,360 --> 00:27:28,920
Before coming here, I said I was tough.

765
00:27:29,160 --> 00:27:30,920
But in those 11 days on the island,

766
00:27:30,920 --> 00:27:32,100
I cried for four or five days.

767
00:27:32,720 --> 00:27:35,960
I care a lot about doing things perfectly.

768
00:27:35,960 --> 00:27:37,840
But I messed up a lot.

769
00:27:38,440 --> 00:27:41,520
So often, the more I fear or care

770
00:27:41,520 --> 00:27:42,320
about something,

771
00:27:42,320 --> 00:27:44,840
the more it seems to happen.

772
00:27:46,960 --> 00:27:48,560
But I was incredibly lucky.

773
00:27:49,520 --> 00:27:51,840
When I was drowning,

774
00:27:51,920 --> 00:27:54,440
my feet couldn't touch the bottom

775
00:27:54,440 --> 00:27:56,880
and my hands couldn't reach the edge,

776
00:27:56,880 --> 00:27:58,240
Zhang Zizheng saved me.

777
00:27:59,040 --> 00:28:03,320
And the day I lost all my votes,

778
00:28:03,680 --> 00:28:05,840
(Day 4, after our date)
someone stepped in to protect me.

779
00:28:06,040 --> 00:28:07,440
(Day 5, before the Balance Vote)
From now on, I'm like your brother.

780
00:28:07,640 --> 00:28:08,680
You're my big brother?

781
00:28:09,040 --> 00:28:09,680
Bro.

782
00:28:10,040 --> 00:28:12,240
Period. You're my little sis now.

783
00:28:12,320 --> 00:28:14,640
When I didn't have Jiaming...

784
00:28:14,640 --> 00:28:17,080
(When Jiaming left on Day 3)
A friend from my real life

785
00:28:17,080 --> 00:28:19,680
who I suddenly lost here...

786
00:28:19,840 --> 00:28:22,560
I welcomed a new roommate

787
00:28:22,560 --> 00:28:25,240
who could handle all my emotions.

788
00:28:25,440 --> 00:28:27,120
Now we're roommates.

789
00:28:27,640 --> 00:28:29,520
You guys brought so much stuff.

790
00:28:30,480 --> 00:28:32,240
That's why I feel so lucky.

791
00:28:33,640 --> 00:28:37,160
If I had to sum up my time here

792
00:28:37,160 --> 00:28:38,280
in one sentence,

793
00:28:38,440 --> 00:28:41,760
I'd say I rediscovered myself.

794
00:28:42,840 --> 00:28:44,840
I'm not as strong as I thought.

795
00:28:45,040 --> 00:28:47,080
Not as bold as I imagined.

796
00:28:47,760 --> 00:28:48,680
But I'm still

797
00:28:48,680 --> 00:28:51,120
full of life.

798
00:28:51,920 --> 00:28:53,440
I'm willing to accept

799
00:28:55,080 --> 00:28:56,880
whatever comes my way.

800
00:28:57,840 --> 00:28:59,880
Even after 11 days

801
00:28:59,880 --> 00:29:01,040
of emotional rollercoaster,

802
00:29:01,040 --> 00:29:02,640
I can still tell myself

803
00:29:03,080 --> 00:29:04,880
that I absolutely love who I am.

804
00:29:05,040 --> 00:29:06,000
I'm still

805
00:29:06,000 --> 00:29:07,680
proud of myself.

806
00:29:16,640 --> 00:29:18,920
All gatherings eventually end.

807
00:29:18,920 --> 00:29:22,320
Well, our Balance Island trip is wrapping up.

808
00:29:23,160 --> 00:29:26,440
Some might leave with a sense of regret.

809
00:29:26,960 --> 00:29:29,720
Some will part ways with joy.

810
00:29:30,240 --> 00:29:33,400
I hope you

811
00:29:34,520 --> 00:29:36,440
stay happy long after you leave.

812
00:29:36,440 --> 00:29:39,640
And we'll

813
00:29:39,640 --> 00:29:41,360
leave our regrets on Balance Island

814
00:29:41,440 --> 00:29:44,720
and be happy when we get back to real life.

815
00:29:44,720 --> 00:29:45,440
You bet.

816
00:29:45,440 --> 00:29:46,040
Cheers.

817
00:29:46,440 --> 00:29:48,320
For sure.

818
00:29:48,320 --> 00:29:49,960
Let's drink to that.

819
00:29:53,680 --> 00:29:56,360
These past days have
been truly unforgettable.

820
00:29:56,680 --> 00:29:58,040
From being the first one

821
00:30:02,480 --> 00:30:03,880
to arrive on Day 1...

822
00:30:03,880 --> 00:30:06,360
Hi everyone.

823
00:30:06,640 --> 00:30:09,160
To working hard as the village chief.

824
00:30:09,160 --> 00:30:10,920
Alright, travelers, follow me.

825
00:30:11,240 --> 00:30:13,760
To witnessing their love stories.

826
00:30:13,960 --> 00:30:14,840
I like you.

827
00:30:20,880 --> 00:30:22,480
Everything from you feels so sweet.

828
00:30:24,760 --> 00:30:26,120
You really have to say it in front

829
00:30:26,120 --> 00:30:27,000
of the three of us?

830
00:30:28,040 --> 00:30:30,080
I do have some regrets.

831
00:30:30,760 --> 00:30:31,640
But I'm really happy.

832
00:30:33,600 --> 00:30:34,480
I'm the host.

833
00:30:38,160 --> 00:30:39,440
Fast enough?

834
00:30:40,080 --> 00:30:41,600
I think getting to know you all

835
00:30:41,680 --> 00:30:44,000
and staying together in the same space,

836
00:30:44,000 --> 00:30:45,360
living under one roof,

837
00:30:45,360 --> 00:30:46,680
makes me happy.

838
00:30:46,680 --> 00:30:47,920
Getting to be friends

839
00:30:47,920 --> 00:30:49,720
with people as amazing as you—

840
00:30:49,720 --> 00:30:51,360
both inside and out...

841
00:30:51,360 --> 00:30:52,920
It's been an absolute honor.

842
00:30:52,920 --> 00:30:53,720
That's it.

843
00:31:06,920 --> 00:31:08,840
See? I told you.

844
00:31:09,760 --> 00:31:11,680
My bad.

845
00:31:12,040 --> 00:31:12,960
I'm done.

846
00:31:12,960 --> 00:31:13,680
I'm so done.

847
00:31:13,680 --> 00:31:15,640
I'm so done.

848
00:31:16,320 --> 00:31:17,680
That's hilarious.

849
00:31:17,680 --> 00:31:18,440
I'm so done.

850
00:31:18,440 --> 00:31:20,400
I have to fix my wispy bangs.

851
00:31:24,320 --> 00:31:26,040
Your man is top-tier.

852
00:31:26,040 --> 00:31:27,920
Your guys aren't too bad either.

853
00:31:34,120 --> 00:31:37,240
I'm so grateful for Balance Island.

854
00:31:37,240 --> 00:31:38,560
It gave me

855
00:31:38,560 --> 00:31:42,360
these once-in-a-lifetime memories.

856
00:31:42,360 --> 00:31:44,440
I just want to say I love you all.

857
00:31:44,440 --> 00:31:45,440
I love Balance Island.

858
00:31:45,560 --> 00:31:46,720
I love every one of you.

859
00:31:50,080 --> 00:31:51,280
I'm genuinely happy

860
00:31:51,280 --> 00:31:53,000
to have had this experience.

861
00:31:53,480 --> 00:31:54,640
This experience will

862
00:31:54,640 --> 00:31:57,040
stay with me for life.

863
00:32:04,280 --> 00:32:05,120
Let's go.

864
00:32:05,120 --> 00:32:06,200
Back to the rooms, guys.

865
00:32:06,200 --> 00:32:06,720
Let's go.

866
00:32:06,880 --> 00:32:08,200
It's about time to confess.

867
00:32:08,320 --> 00:32:09,720
Better go get ready.

868
00:32:09,920 --> 00:32:11,120
It's raining.

869
00:32:11,120 --> 00:32:12,080
I need an umbrella.

870
00:32:12,480 --> 00:32:12,880
Sorry.

871
00:32:13,320 --> 00:32:15,200
Go. Go. Go.

872
00:32:16,560 --> 00:32:17,600
So many flowers.

873
00:32:18,240 --> 00:32:19,480
Flowers for you.

874
00:32:20,240 --> 00:32:21,000
You're so sweet.

875
00:32:21,200 --> 00:32:23,000
When will you send me

876
00:32:23,000 --> 00:32:24,010
a huge bunch of flowers?

877
00:32:24,080 --> 00:32:25,120
Maybe at your funeral.

878
00:32:25,280 --> 00:32:26,280
Shut up. Take it back.

879
00:32:26,280 --> 00:32:27,520
Hurry. Take it back.

880
00:32:28,000 --> 00:32:29,280
Take it back.

881
00:32:29,280 --> 00:32:29,680
Come on.

882
00:32:29,680 --> 00:32:30,440
Hurry up.

883
00:32:30,440 --> 00:32:31,120
I take it back.

884
00:32:31,480 --> 00:32:32,240
Seriously.

885
00:32:33,560 --> 00:32:34,400
Bye-bye.

886
00:32:34,400 --> 00:32:34,960
Bye-bye.

887
00:32:40,400 --> 00:32:41,240
Simple.

888
00:32:45,960 --> 00:32:46,960
You ready?

889
00:32:47,760 --> 00:32:48,600
Yes.

890
00:32:48,600 --> 00:32:49,440
Wanna run it once?

891
00:32:49,680 --> 00:32:51,160
(Rehearsal)
No.

892
00:32:51,160 --> 00:32:52,000
(Keep it secret)
It's just for her.

893
00:32:52,160 --> 00:32:53,240
What do you mean?

894
00:32:53,240 --> 00:32:54,880
I'm just telling her my feelings.

895
00:32:54,880 --> 00:32:56,980
(Only tell Han)

896
00:32:57,040 --> 00:32:58,960
Will you say "I love you" to her?

897
00:32:58,960 --> 00:33:00,160
(Want a sneak peek)

898
00:33:00,160 --> 00:33:01,160
Not telling you.

899
00:33:01,660 --> 00:33:03,220
(Mystery)

900
00:33:08,680 --> 00:33:10,160
About to confess my feelings.

901
00:33:10,280 --> 00:33:11,560
So nervous right now.

902
00:33:11,560 --> 00:33:12,680
Hope I don't forget my lines.

903
00:33:12,700 --> 00:33:14,360
That's why I've been practicing.

904
00:33:14,760 --> 00:33:17,000
I can't mess up at the big moment.

905
00:33:20,680 --> 00:33:24,440
I'm hoping for a passionate confession.

906
00:33:25,160 --> 00:33:28,080
I'm wearing the lipstick

907
00:33:30,760 --> 00:33:32,000
Han got us

908
00:33:32,240 --> 00:33:33,360
for the big moment.

909
00:33:34,200 --> 00:33:36,480
Yijia got me these heels.

910
00:33:36,840 --> 00:33:37,840
They have a serious heel,

911
00:33:38,200 --> 00:33:40,160
so the height gap between me and Enda

912
00:33:40,160 --> 00:33:41,240
isn't that insane.

913
00:33:42,040 --> 00:33:43,000
You ready?

914
00:33:43,000 --> 00:33:44,200
I'm so nervous.

915
00:33:47,960 --> 00:33:51,040
Still debating if I should ditch the script.

916
00:33:51,040 --> 00:33:52,760
Turns out, that's harder than I thought.

917
00:33:52,760 --> 00:33:54,280
Because I've got too much to say.

918
00:33:55,240 --> 00:33:56,560
But I'm feeling good.

919
00:33:56,560 --> 00:33:58,560
Because all the memories I recall

920
00:33:58,560 --> 00:33:59,560
are good ones.

921
00:33:59,680 --> 00:34:02,080
I'm getting all the happy feels just

922
00:34:02,080 --> 00:34:02,960
writing this down.

923
00:34:04,200 --> 00:34:07,400
♪There are always unexpected encounters♪

924
00:34:07,400 --> 00:34:08,480
I'd cry. So touching.

925
00:34:08,480 --> 00:34:12,640
♪Right at the moment I meet you♪

926
00:34:12,880 --> 00:34:19,600
♪Those gentle and clear eyes of yours♪

927
00:34:20,520 --> 00:34:22,960
♪Appeared in my dreams♪

928
00:34:28,680 --> 00:34:30,950
The village chief said he doesn't mind
being called ugly.

929
00:34:30,970 --> 00:34:32,560
His only fear is being unwanted.

930
00:34:33,760 --> 00:34:35,680
Just thinking about that makes me laugh.

931
00:34:35,680 --> 00:34:37,160
I don't care about being single.

932
00:34:37,160 --> 00:34:39,040
Just don't call me old or ugly.

933
00:34:40,420 --> 00:34:45,860
(10 minutes until the final confession)

934
00:34:45,940 --> 00:34:49,820
(8 minutes until the final confession)

935
00:34:49,900 --> 00:34:55,500
(5 minutes until the final confession)

936
00:34:55,500 --> 00:34:58,460
(4 minutes until the final confession,
Square)

937
00:34:58,460 --> 00:35:01,180
(3 minutes until the final confession)

938
00:35:01,180 --> 00:35:03,860
(2 minutes until the final confession)

939
00:35:03,860 --> 00:35:06,980
(1 minutes until the final confession)

940
00:35:07,060 --> 00:35:12,460
(0 minutes until the final confession)

941
00:35:24,800 --> 00:35:27,040
I've always had this

942
00:35:27,040 --> 00:35:30,440
super idealistic view of love.

943
00:35:32,520 --> 00:35:34,080
The village chief said

944
00:35:34,080 --> 00:35:36,880
my idea of romance was a bit naive.

945
00:35:37,200 --> 00:35:39,080
But I still believe that kind of love

946
00:35:39,080 --> 00:35:39,920
is out there.

947
00:35:40,480 --> 00:35:41,640
At this point,

948
00:35:41,640 --> 00:35:44,000
walking away with these friends

949
00:35:44,000 --> 00:35:45,840
means the world to me.

950
00:36:11,880 --> 00:36:14,800
It's a shame I didn't meet someone I liked

951
00:36:14,800 --> 00:36:16,080
who liked me back on the island.

952
00:36:17,480 --> 00:36:19,600
It's a bit of a bummer.

953
00:36:19,600 --> 00:36:23,000
I think timing in life matters a lot,

954
00:36:23,120 --> 00:36:24,920
and it can change so many things.

955
00:36:25,720 --> 00:36:27,480
But that's alright.

956
00:36:27,480 --> 00:36:30,320
I believe the right connection will come

957
00:36:30,320 --> 00:36:31,920
when the timing is just right.

958
00:36:37,400 --> 00:36:39,880
A little bit of regret, I guess.

959
00:36:40,200 --> 00:36:41,360
Didn't find

960
00:36:41,360 --> 00:36:43,680
the one here.

961
00:36:44,000 --> 00:36:45,720
Maybe it's all meant to be.

962
00:36:45,720 --> 00:36:47,040
It's all about fate.

963
00:36:48,120 --> 00:36:49,000
But I also believe

964
00:36:49,000 --> 00:36:51,400
that my love will eventually come.

965
00:36:52,120 --> 00:36:53,960
Looking sharp.

966
00:36:54,480 --> 00:36:55,640
Killing it.

967
00:36:56,040 --> 00:36:56,720
Thank you.

968
00:37:21,800 --> 00:37:25,200
This might be the scene
I've always dreamed of.

969
00:37:31,920 --> 00:37:35,400
I want to tell Jiayi something.

970
00:37:36,080 --> 00:37:40,000
If I get the chance,
I'd love to know her better.

971
00:37:42,600 --> 00:37:44,320
These 11 days of the journey

972
00:37:44,320 --> 00:37:45,200
feel like a dream.

973
00:37:45,920 --> 00:37:48,840
Every feeling I had was tied to Jiayi.

974
00:37:49,440 --> 00:37:50,600
The happy ones.

975
00:37:50,600 --> 00:37:51,640
(The happy ones)

976
00:37:51,640 --> 00:37:52,800
Dachshund.

977
00:37:52,800 --> 00:37:53,160
Yeah.

978
00:37:53,160 --> 00:37:53,640
My favorite.

979
00:37:53,640 --> 00:37:54,560
Really?

980
00:37:54,560 --> 00:37:55,720
When I'm in a relationship,

981
00:37:55,720 --> 00:37:56,760
I want to keep one.

982
00:37:56,760 --> 00:37:57,680
I choose you.

983
00:37:57,920 --> 00:37:58,920
Are you happy?

984
00:37:59,120 --> 00:38:00,480
How could I not be?

985
00:38:01,720 --> 00:38:04,040
If I were a guy, I'd try car racing too.

986
00:38:05,080 --> 00:38:06,400
But my driving's bad.

987
00:38:06,400 --> 00:38:08,600
It's fine. I'll be your chauffeur.

988
00:38:09,280 --> 00:38:11,000
You're a great driver.

989
00:38:11,000 --> 00:38:12,520
The pro moves are showing.

990
00:38:12,840 --> 00:38:14,600
If I don't get eliminated tomorrow...

991
00:38:14,640 --> 00:38:16,080
No way. I won't let that happen.

992
00:38:16,080 --> 00:38:17,120
Don't worry about it.

993
00:38:18,200 --> 00:38:20,520
The jealous ones.

994
00:38:20,840 --> 00:38:24,600
(Jealous ones)
Is this one bowl enough?

995
00:38:24,600 --> 00:38:26,040
Yeah, that's perfect.

996
00:38:29,200 --> 00:38:32,120
I've already forgotten my next line.

997
00:38:36,280 --> 00:38:37,480
And sad ones too.

998
00:38:38,000 --> 00:38:41,400
(Sad ones)
Did you have fun on our date yesterday?

999
00:38:41,400 --> 00:38:42,240
I did.

1000
00:38:42,240 --> 00:38:43,400
That was a lie.

1001
00:38:45,000 --> 00:38:46,840
Do you still want to know me better?

1002
00:38:47,000 --> 00:38:47,840
I don't plan to.

1003
00:38:49,600 --> 00:38:51,920
Did I force you to put in all that effort?

1004
00:38:51,920 --> 00:38:53,520
If you're tired, then just stop.

1005
00:38:55,280 --> 00:38:57,120
But I don't regret

1006
00:38:57,120 --> 00:38:58,840
a single second I spent on her.

1007
00:39:04,240 --> 00:39:05,200
I picked it myself.

1008
00:39:06,680 --> 00:39:08,000
It looks really nice.

1009
00:39:08,000 --> 00:39:09,000
A totally different vibe.

1010
00:39:09,200 --> 00:39:11,400
Feeling completely surrounded by love.

1011
00:39:11,600 --> 00:39:12,920
You can tuck it behind your ear.

1012
00:39:12,920 --> 00:39:14,200
It's really pretty.

1013
00:39:14,440 --> 00:39:15,800
I made breakfast for you.

1014
00:39:16,360 --> 00:39:17,200
You're so sweet.

1015
00:39:17,480 --> 00:39:18,400
Only for you.

1016
00:39:18,800 --> 00:39:20,280
I feel so happy right now.

1017
00:39:20,280 --> 00:39:21,600
If you're happy, I'm happy.

1018
00:39:24,800 --> 00:39:27,480
I've never gone all-out for a girl.

1019
00:39:27,920 --> 00:39:31,200
It's a first for me.

1020
00:39:31,440 --> 00:39:32,480
For me,

1021
00:39:32,600 --> 00:39:35,080
no matter how it ends, I won't regret it.

1022
00:39:45,840 --> 00:39:48,200
I'm choosing not to confess today.

1023
00:39:48,600 --> 00:39:50,640
Because loving someone,

1024
00:39:50,640 --> 00:39:53,200
sometimes means learning to let go.

1025
00:39:54,040 --> 00:39:57,920
(One hour ago)
I have two more things for Jiayi.

1026
00:39:58,640 --> 00:40:00,840
One is this little mug,

1027
00:40:01,280 --> 00:40:03,200
since you don't like cold water.

1028
00:40:03,400 --> 00:40:05,640
And the second was a small card.

1029
00:40:06,400 --> 00:40:07,680
To Jiayi.

1030
00:40:07,680 --> 00:40:10,320
Meeting you was the best part of this trip.

1031
00:40:10,320 --> 00:40:13,000
Thanks for being part of this memory.

1032
00:40:13,280 --> 00:40:15,000
May we both find happiness in the future.

1033
00:40:15,240 --> 00:40:17,920
I want you to stay happy,

1034
00:40:17,920 --> 00:40:19,400
stay blessed,

1035
00:40:19,600 --> 00:40:20,920
and stay as adorable as you are.

1036
00:40:58,560 --> 00:41:00,800
Sucks that it's not me standing there.

1037
00:41:03,760 --> 00:41:04,320
Here we go.

1038
00:41:04,480 --> 00:41:06,280
Who is it?

1039
00:41:16,120 --> 00:41:18,200
Walking over there,

1040
00:41:18,200 --> 00:41:21,120
I was wondering how it's all gonna end.

1041
00:41:23,400 --> 00:41:24,360
I was so curious

1042
00:41:24,360 --> 00:41:26,880
to see how he'd show up,

1043
00:41:26,880 --> 00:41:27,610
what he'd say,

1044
00:41:27,630 --> 00:41:28,560
or what kind of gift

1045
00:41:28,560 --> 00:41:29,880
he had waiting for me.

1046
00:41:31,160 --> 00:41:32,400
I was also wondering

1047
00:41:32,400 --> 00:41:34,080
what kind of confession it would be.

1048
00:41:34,360 --> 00:41:36,880
Like, a "let's keep

1049
00:41:36,880 --> 00:41:37,880
seeing each other" thing,

1050
00:41:37,880 --> 00:41:39,400
or a "let's be official" thing.

1051
00:42:00,280 --> 00:42:04,000
I was pretty chill
walking down the stairs.

1052
00:42:04,800 --> 00:42:07,080
Once I saw her smiling

1053
00:42:07,080 --> 00:42:08,280
in the distance,

1054
00:42:08,360 --> 00:42:09,920
I felt way more at ease.

1055
00:42:11,400 --> 00:42:12,880
But the closer I got,

1056
00:42:12,880 --> 00:42:14,400
the more the nerves started kicking in.

1057
00:42:16,480 --> 00:42:17,680
(Good morning)
Morning.

1058
00:42:18,400 --> 00:42:19,320
(Good night)
Night.

1059
00:42:20,280 --> 00:42:21,680
You're looking very sharp today.

1060
00:42:22,560 --> 00:42:23,160
You too.

1061
00:42:32,160 --> 00:42:32,960
I can't see.

1062
00:42:32,960 --> 00:42:33,960
It's killing me.

1063
00:42:34,080 --> 00:42:34,880
Want to take a look?

1064
00:42:35,080 --> 00:42:36,000
Of course.

1065
00:42:36,000 --> 00:42:37,560
Then let's head up that hill.

1066
00:42:38,080 --> 00:42:38,920
Is that okay?

1067
00:42:39,160 --> 00:42:40,120
Can we go?

1068
00:42:40,120 --> 00:42:40,720
Let's go.

1069
00:42:41,280 --> 00:42:41,880
That hill?

1070
00:42:42,080 --> 00:42:43,400
Yeah, let's head up.

1071
00:42:47,940 --> 00:42:49,140
(Sneaking around)

1072
00:42:49,160 --> 00:42:50,680
A crowd of curious onlookers.

1073
00:42:56,040 --> 00:42:56,480
Tianyu.

1074
00:42:57,240 --> 00:42:57,880
Tianyu?

1075
00:42:57,960 --> 00:42:58,320
Yeah.

1076
00:42:58,440 --> 00:42:59,320
That's Han.

1077
00:43:00,320 --> 00:43:01,480
So jealous. It's so romantic.

1078
00:43:02,880 --> 00:43:04,000
This view is legit.

1079
00:43:04,000 --> 00:43:05,920
(Taking the high ground)
We just can't hear them.

1080
00:43:05,920 --> 00:43:06,720
Yeah.

1081
00:43:07,720 --> 00:43:09,400
Have you ever been confessed to before?

1082
00:43:09,400 --> 00:43:10,080
Well...

1083
00:43:10,080 --> 00:43:12,080
Not in such a formal setting.

1084
00:43:18,920 --> 00:43:19,760
What's on your mind?

1085
00:43:21,360 --> 00:43:21,880
I'm not sure.

1086
00:43:21,880 --> 00:43:22,520
I feel...

1087
00:43:23,800 --> 00:43:24,680
A little nervous.

1088
00:43:26,680 --> 00:43:27,960
Do you get nervous too?

1089
00:43:28,560 --> 00:43:29,680
Totally.

1090
00:43:43,960 --> 00:43:45,600
I've got a few gifts for you.

1091
00:43:47,280 --> 00:43:47,960
First...

1092
00:43:48,480 --> 00:43:49,320
Didn't you say...

1093
00:43:49,320 --> 00:43:50,400
Don't look yet.

1094
00:43:51,560 --> 00:43:53,960
The first is a flower.

1095
00:43:55,260 --> 00:43:57,100
(A rose)

1096
00:43:58,440 --> 00:43:59,840
It carries a meaning.

1097
00:43:59,840 --> 00:44:00,440
First off...

1098
00:44:00,470 --> 00:44:01,000
I built

1099
00:44:01,000 --> 00:44:02,360
this rose myself in the dining room

1100
00:44:02,360 --> 00:44:03,200
yesterday.

1101
00:44:06,140 --> 00:44:14,420
(Last night)

1102
00:44:16,040 --> 00:44:20,200
I chose it because

1103
00:44:21,760 --> 00:44:22,960
it'll never wilt.

1104
00:44:23,500 --> 00:44:25,900
(An everlasting rose)

1105
00:44:27,600 --> 00:44:31,640
And compared to real flowers,

1106
00:44:31,760 --> 00:44:33,320
it has edges. It's got character.

1107
00:44:33,360 --> 00:44:34,920
Just like our personalities.

1108
00:44:35,900 --> 00:44:41,660
(An angular rose just like the two of us.)

1109
00:44:42,880 --> 00:44:43,840
And then,

1110
00:44:44,240 --> 00:44:46,360
I got you a bottle of perfume.

1111
00:44:46,920 --> 00:44:50,640
Because I believe scent

1112
00:44:50,920 --> 00:44:52,160
can trigger

1113
00:44:53,280 --> 00:44:55,200
the strongest memories.

1114
00:44:55,520 --> 00:44:57,320
I want you

1115
00:44:57,320 --> 00:44:59,360
to think of me

1116
00:44:59,760 --> 00:45:01,120
whenever we're apart.

1117
00:45:03,320 --> 00:45:04,200
Here.

1118
00:45:04,200 --> 00:45:04,640
Thank you.

1119
00:45:05,360 --> 00:45:07,760
And a lip balm.

1120
00:45:09,080 --> 00:45:10,720
The one you always use.

1121
00:45:10,720 --> 00:45:11,520
Thanks.

1122
00:45:11,520 --> 00:45:12,200
So thoughtful.

1123
00:45:12,200 --> 00:45:13,160
Really.

1124
00:45:17,720 --> 00:45:18,640
And one last thing.

1125
00:45:27,960 --> 00:45:29,160
A photo of us.

1126
00:45:33,320 --> 00:45:35,000
Three, two, one.

1127
00:45:35,000 --> 00:45:36,400
(Day 6)

1128
00:45:36,400 --> 00:45:37,190
Gonna look great.

1129
00:45:37,210 --> 00:45:37,800
I think so too.

1130
00:45:39,200 --> 00:45:40,360
(Half an hour ago)
Does this photo frame look nice?

1131
00:45:40,360 --> 00:45:41,400
Yeah.

1132
00:45:41,520 --> 00:45:42,640
You can tell we're in love.

1133
00:45:42,880 --> 00:45:43,920
Yeah, totally.

1134
00:45:48,360 --> 00:45:49,200
Thanks.

1135
00:45:50,160 --> 00:45:50,800
Do you like it?

1136
00:45:50,800 --> 00:45:51,720
I really do.

1137
00:45:54,120 --> 00:45:55,160
It's pretty touching.

1138
00:45:55,400 --> 00:45:58,000
She put so much thought into these.

1139
00:45:58,120 --> 00:45:59,800
She didn't have to say much,

1140
00:45:59,800 --> 00:46:02,720
but the gifts

1141
00:46:02,720 --> 00:46:04,920
spoke for themselves.

1142
00:46:04,920 --> 00:46:06,320
I definitely got the message.

1143
00:46:07,960 --> 00:46:10,920
What I really wanted to say is

1144
